					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Hi.<br /><br />Hypothetical scenario. Let's say I do this a bank switch:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">lda xxx<br />sta $8000<br />; NMI triggers here<br />lda yyy<br />sta $8001<br /></div><br /><br />And the NMI triggers between the 8000/8001. Lets say the NMI also does bank switches for audio and other things. Lets also assume the NMI is being nice and pushing/popping all registers. <br /><br />What will happen when the code resumes and does that 8001 store?<br />Will it do anything, will it be ignored?<br /><br />I read that it is good practice to first store the bank you want to switch to to a variable, so you can restore all banks at the end of NMI to prevent these kind of issues. Does it apply to this exact scenario?<br /><br />Thanks.<br /><br />-Mat</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

