				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yeah from the point of view of MMC3 it doesn't know that an NMI happened, it's just interpreting the writes sequentially.<br /><br />This situation is fairly easy to deal with when it comes to MMC3. Some other mappers like MMC1 are more annoying (if an interrupt can happen in the middle of the 5-bit write sequence, you have to detect that situation and resume from the beginning).</div>

					
