				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Oh thank you guys. I get it now.<br /><br />For some reason I always though bank swap always required a pair of writes (8000 + 8001) but that's not the case. The value of the 8000 persists until it is modified, so that's the only value that you need to shadow (and restore at the end of NMI) to prevent that case from being a problem. Easy. <br /><br />Thanks again. <br /><br />-Mat</div>

