						<div class="postbody">It's not a technique for MMC1, and probably not MMC3 either.<br /><br />It's useful for e.g. UxROM or AxROM that have more atomic state, if you need to bankswitch in an IRQ or NMI you can inspect the bank number to know what to put back afterward.<br /><br /><em>Edit: tokumaru was suggesting a diffferent technique than I thought: verify and retry. See below.</em></div>

					
